OL,3,C'Bionic peer' thanks wife who rejected
OL,4,Cdo not resuscitate order
OL,6,F"Bionic peer" Lord Mackinley of
OL,7,FRichborough has paid tribute to his
OL,8,Fwife for keeping him alive, in his
OL,9,Fmaiden speech in the House of Lords,
OL,10,Fas he said he would campaign for
OL,11,Famputees to have quicker access to
OL,12,Fhigher quality prosthetics.
OL,14,FThe Conservative member of the upper
OL,15,Fchamber was given a 5% chance of
OL,16,Fliving when he got sepsis in September
OL,17,Flast year, and had all his limbs
OL,18,Famputated in early December.
OL,26,@nD@AOUnD@MO]
