OL,3,C'Bionic peer' thanks wife who rejected
OL,4,Cdo not resuscitate order
OL,6,FIn his first speech in the upper
OL,7,Fchamber Lord Mackinley thanked his
OL,8,Fwife Kati for not signing a do not
OL,9,Fresuscitate order or agreeing to end-
OL,10,Fof-life care when he was being treated
OL,11,Fat St Thomas' Hospital.
OL,13,FHe said: "I am particularly grateful
OL,14,Fto be in this place and very, very
OL,15,Flucky, because just over a year ago my
OL,16,Fluck had sincerely run out.
