OL,3,C'Bionic peer' thanks wife who rejected
OL,4,Cdo not resuscitate order
OL,6,FThe 58-year-old was treated in
OL,7,Fhospital for seven months. He returned
OL,8,Fto Parliament in May and received a
OL,9,Frare standing ovation from fellow MPs.
OL,11,FThe peer has since described himself
OL,12,Fas the "bionic lord" on an episode of
OL,13,Fthe Sepsis Voices with Dr Ron podcast,
OL,14,Fproduced by the charity UK Sepsis
OL,15,FTrust.
OL,17,FLord Mackinlay said he would be
OL,18,Fraising awareness of the condition and
OL,19,Ftrying to secure quicker access to
OL,20,Fbetter quality prosthetics.
OL,26,@tD@HOUtD@TO]
