OL,3,C'Bionic peer' thanks wife who rejected
OL,4,Cdo not resuscitate order
OL,6,F"But many people do lose bits and
OL,7,Fpieces. They might lose a few fingers,
OL,8,Fthey might lose a bit of a foot, I was
OL,9,Fvery unfortunate because of the extent
OL,10,Fof the clotting that I lost all four
OL,11,Flimbs."
OL,13,FThe peer added: "But after that, after
OL,14,Fthe NHS having spent many hundreds of
OL,15,Fpounds keeping me alive over a very
OL,16,Flong period, you then come to the
OL,17,Fposition of, 'What shall we do to get
OL,18,Fpeople like me on their feet? Do we
OL,19,Fprovide them with appropriate
OL,20,Fprosthetics'.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@GO]uD@QOU
